name: Sheet Pan Steak and Shrimp Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'sirloin steak, sliced 1/4-inch thick across the grain'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, halved'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh cilantro sprigs'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(8-inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line 2 sheet pans with parchment paper or aluminum foil.. Combine chili powder, smoked paprika, oregano, salt, cumin, garlic powder, and cayenne in a small bowl.. In a large bowl, combine green bell pepper, red bell pepper, and onion with 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil and 1/2 of dry seasoning mixture. Toss until evenly coated with seasoning mixture and spread out in a single layer on one of the prepared pans.. Meanwhile, in the same large bowl, toss steak and shrimp with remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil; add remaining seasoning and toss again. Place steak on one side of second prepared pan, with shrimp on the other side of pan.. Place steak and shrimp on a rack below vegetables and roast both pans for 10 minutes. After 10 minutes, swap rack positions of the pans, bringing the lower pan up, and placing the other pan on the rack below. Continue roasting until shrimp is pink and tightly curled, steak is cooked to medium, and vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes more. An instant read thermometer inserted in center of steak should read 140 degrees F (60 degrees C) . If steak or vegetables require more time, remove shrimp to a plate and keep warm, while other ingredients continue cooking. Squeeze juice of half a lime over contents of each sheet pan.. To serve: Place a few steak strips, onion and pepper strips, 2 shrimp, and some cilantro on each tortilla. Roll up tortillas and contents jelly-roll fashion, and enjoy!

name: Skillet Shrimp Fajitas with Cilantro-Lime Cream
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'limes, zested and juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green pepper, sliced vertically'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red pepper, sliced vertically'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'avocado oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, juiced, divided'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': None, 'name': 'flour tortillas, warmed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado - peeled, pitted, and sliced (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pico de gallo, (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'fresh cilantro, chopped (optional)'}
steps: For cilantro-lime cream, place sour cream in a small bowl with a lid. Add cilantro, zest and juice of 2 limes, garlic, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir together well, cover, and refrigerate until ready to serve.. For fajita seasoning, combine chili powder, cayenne pepper, cumin, paprika, oregano, salt and pepper in a small bowl; set aside.. In a large bowl or resealable plastic bag, add 2 tablespoons oil, half of lime juice, and fajita seasoning. Stir together or squeeze the bag to combine. Add shrimp and mix well to coat shrimp; set aside.. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Stir onion and peppers into the hot oil, and cook, stirring frequently, until some color begins to develop on the vegetables, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove vegetables from the skillet and set aside.. Add shrimp to the same skillet and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Return cooked vegetables to the skillet. Cook and stir until shrimp is opaque and pink, 2 to 3 minutes. Squeeze remaining lime juice over the skillet contents.. Fill warm tortillas with shrimp, peppers, and onions, and garnish with avocado slices, pico de gallo, and additional cilantro, if desired. Drizzle with cilantro-lime cream.

name: Chicken Fajita Skillet Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'poblano peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'orange bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes and green chiles'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rotisserie chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce)', 'name': 'can pinto beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lettuce'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Heat oil in a large, oven proof skillet over medium-high heat. Add peppers and onions and cook, undisturbed, 5 minutes or until browned. Add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, salt and pepper and continue cooking until vegetables are soft, stirring often, 1 to 2  minutes. Remove vegetables from the pan and set aside.. Add butter to the pan and melt over moderate heat. Whisk in flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add in tomatoes and broth and cook until thick and creamy, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes. Stir in chicken and beans. Top chicken mixture with 1 cup cheese. Spread reserved peppers and onions evenly over the cheese and top with chips and remaining cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven until bubbly and lightly browned on top, about 15  minutes. Serve with desired toppings.

name: Chicken Fajita Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'orange juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'taco seasoning (see Note)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken breasts, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green bell pepper, seeded and cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell pepper, seeded and cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '6 inch', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado, pitted and sliced, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cotija cheese, or as needed'}
steps: Combine orange juice, taco seasoning, and vegetable oil in a large resealable bag. Add chicken, coat with the marinade, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator overnight.. Heat a cast iron skillet over medium high heat.. Cook chicken in the hot skillet for 5 minutes. Add onion, green bell pepper, and red bell pepper. Cook until peppers are crisp tender, 4 to 5 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into center of chicken strips should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Heat tortillas until soft and pliable. Top with chicken fajita mixture, avocado, sour cream, and cotija cheese. Serve immediately.

name: Sheet Pan Chicken Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'chicken tenders, quartered'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sliced bell peppers, any color'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, sliced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, juiced'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Combine oil, chili powder, oregano, garlic powder, onion powder, cumin, salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper in a large resealable plastic bag. Add chicken tenders, bell peppers, and onion; seal the bag and shake to mix. Marinate in the refrigerator, 30 minutes to 2 hours.. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a rimmed sheet pan with aluminum foil.. Spread chicken mixture onto the prepared pan.. Roast in the preheated oven, stirring halfway, until chicken is no longer pink and bell peppers are softened, 15 to 20 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of chicken should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Sprinkle cilantro and pour lime juice over chicken mixture; stir to distribute.

name: Beef Fajitas

steps: Whisk oil, lime juice, cilantro, onion, garlic, cumin, salt, and pepper together in a bowl; pour into a resealable plastic bag. Add steak strips, coat with marinade, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator for 4 to 8 hours.. When ready to cook, heat a large skillet over medium heat. Add steak and marinade; cook and stir until steak is browned and cooked through and all liquid is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.. Serve steak on tortillas with salsa and Mexican cheese.

name: Slow Cooker Steak Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 1/2 pound)', 'name': 'beef flank steak, cut into six equal portions'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'chopped tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, sliced into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, sliced into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeño pepper, seeded and chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'flour tortillas, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend'}
steps: Place flank steak pieces into a slow cooker. Stir in tomatoes, onion, bell peppers, jalapeño pepper, garlic, chili powder, cumin, coriander, and salt.. Cook on Low for 8 to 10 hours or High for 4 to 6 hours, until steak is fall-apart tender.. Remove steak from the slow cooker and shred. Return to the slow cooker and stir into the sauce.. Serve hot with tortillas and shredded cheese, allowing everyone to make their own fajita.

name: Homemade Chicken Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bell peppers, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Whisk chili powder, paprika, salt, pepper, cayenne pepper, and garlic powder for fajita seasoning together in a small bowl.. Trim chicken of any excess fat and place in a large, lidded bowl. Add 2 tablespoons olive oil and sprinkle with about 3/4 of the fajita seasoning. Toss, adding more oil if necessary, until coated. Poke chicken with a knife to allow penetration of seasoning and oil. Place the lid on the bowl and shake until chicken is thoroughly coated. Marinate in the refrigerator, shaking every couple of hours, for 4 to 6 hours.. Remove the marinating bowl from the refrigerator and let sit on the counter until chicken is room temperature, about 1 hour.. Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Make 2 stacks of 4 tortillas, and wrap each one in aluminum foil.. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add peppers and onion. Stir in remaining fajita seasoning and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft, 8 to 10 minutes.. While vegetables are cooking, place tortillas in the oven to warm. At the same time, grill chicken, turning halfway through, until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, 2 to 3 minutes per side.. To assemble fajitas, fill warmed tortillas with chicken, peppers, and onions.

name: Venison Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'seasoned salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'venison, cut into 2 inch strips'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'red bell pepper, cut into 2 inch strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'yellow bell pepper, cut into 2 inch strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, cut into 1/2-inch wedges'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'fajita size flour tortillas, warmed'}
steps: Combine seasoned salt, garlic salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper, and oregano to make the fajita seasoning. Sprinkle two teaspoons of the seasoning over the sliced venison. Mix well, cover, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a heavy frying pan. Cook bell peppers and onion until starting to soften, then remove. Pour in remaining oil, then cook venison until browned. Return pepper mixture to the pan, season with remaining fajita seasoning, and reheat. Served with the warmed tortillas.

name: Cast Iron Chicken Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'freshly squeezed lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'red bell pepper, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'green bell pepper, sliced'}
steps: Make marinade: Combine olive oil, lime juice, chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Add chicken and toss until well coated. Cover the bowl and refrigerate, 4 hours to overnight.. Heat a cast iron skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken to the hot skillet, reserving marinade. Cook until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, 6 to 8 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Remove chicken from the skillet, slice, and set aside.. Cook vegetables: Heat olive oil in the same skillet. Add onion, bell peppers, and reserved marinade. Cook and stir until vegetables are soft and tender, 5 to 7 minutes.. Add chicken back to the skillet; cook and stir until warmed through, 2 to 4 minutes.

name: Steak Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean steak, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh lime juice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'julienned green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemons, quartered'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '(12 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Combine the lime juice, ground pepper and cilantro in a shallow dish. Place steak strips into the marinade and refrigerate for two to four hours.. Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add steak strips, and fry until cooked to your liking. Remove meat and set aside.. Add remaining oil and onions to the skillet. Cook over medium low heat, until translucent, stir in green peppers and steak. Squeeze the juice of 1 lemon over the top and stir. When the green bell peppers are just tender remove the pan from the heat. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve the steak fajitas with tortillas and lemon wedges on the side.

name: Mexican Botana Platter
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'beef skirt steak'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fajita seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'refried beans'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocados — peeled, pitted, and mashed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'corn oil'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': '', 'name': 'corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'cilantro, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'shredded American cheese'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'tomatoes, chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'pickled jalapeño peppers, sliced (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Rub beef and chicken with fajita seasoning and 2 teaspoons garlic powder. Cut beef and chicken into 1-inch strips, and set aside.. Warm refried beans in a saucepan over medium-low heat.. Stir salt, lemon pepper, and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder into mashed avocados. Set aside.. Heat corn oil in a deep skillet over medium-high heat. Cut tortillas in half, then cut in half again to make 4 triangular pieces per tortilla. Place as many tortilla pieces into the skillet as fit without overlapping, and fry until crisp; remove crisp tortillas to paper towels. Repeat this process with remaining tortilla pieces. Discard oil, and wipe out skillet.. Return skillet to medium heat, and stir in beef, chicken, bell pepper, and onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, about 7 minutes, then stir in cilantro.. Layer the tortilla pieces along the bottom of a large baking dish. Spread refried beans evenly over tortilla pieces. Sprinkle cheese over beans, then spread meat mixture evenly on top.. Bake in preheated oven until cheese and beans are bubbly, about 20 minutes. Remove from oven, and drop sour cream and guacamole by tablespoonfuls in various places across the top. Sprinkle tomatoes and jalapeños on top.

name: Air Fryer Steak for Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'jalapeño chile powder (such as Savory Spice Shop) (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'skirt steak, sliced into strips against the grain'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, sliced into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bell pepper, seeded and sliced into strips'}
steps: Combine olive oil, salt, garlic powder, cumin, jalapeño chile powder, chili powder, and coriander in a resealable plastic bag. Add steak, onion, and bell pepper, coat with the marinade, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator for 8 hours to overnight.. Line an air fryer basket with a sheet of perforated parchment paper. Add marinated onion, pepper, and steak.. Air fry for 5 minutes at 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Remove the air fryer basket and shake to ensure even cooking. Air fry until steak is cooked through, about 4 more minutes.

name: Quick and Easy Shrimp Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'medium shrimp - peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': '(1 small) chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1.25 ounce) package', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '(10 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas, warmed'}
steps: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the red and green bell peppers, and onion. Cook, stirring frequently until peppers are hot, but still slightly crisp, about 5 minutes. Remove from the skillet and set aside.. Pour the remaining 1/2 tablespoon of oil into the skillet, and add the shrimp. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pink and opaque. Reduce heat to low, and return the peppers and onion to the skillet. Stir in taco seasoning and water so that everything is evenly coated. Simmer until peppers are heated. Serve in warm tortillas.

name: Karen's Slow Cooker Chicken Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless, skinless chicken breast tenders'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'red bell pepper, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'green bell pepper, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chunky salsa'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(1.4 ounce) packages', 'name': 'fajita seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': '(10 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Shredded cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Chopped tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Guacamole'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Sour cream'}
steps: Open Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner and place it inside a 5- to 6 1/2-quart slow cooker bowl. Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl.. Place chicken in Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner. Place onions and bell peppers on top of chicken.. Mix salsa, fajita seasoning mix and cayenne pepper in a medium bowl. Pour over chicken. Place lid on slow cooker.. Cook on LOW for 6 to 7 hours OR on HIGH for 3 to 4 hours until chicken is done.. Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape. Gently stir chicken and sauce with a plastic or wooden slotted spoon. Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture into center of each tortilla; add desired toppings and fold tortilla over filling. Do not lift or transport liner with food inside. Cool slow cooker completely; remove Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner and toss.

name: Sheet Pan Beef Fajitas

Transfer onion and pepper to a plate.. Heat 1 teaspoon canola oil in the same skillet over high heat until oil starts to smoke. Cook 1/2 of the steak in hot oil until browned on all sides but still pink in the center, 4 to 6 minutes. Transfer cooked steak to the plate with onion and pepper.. Heat remaining canola oil in the same skillet. Cook remaining steak in hot oil until browned on all sides but still pink in the center, 4 to 6 minutes. Stir cooked steak, onion, bell pepper, and any accumulated juices back into the skillet. Add minced garlic and salt; cook and stir until fragrant and heated through. Remove from heat. Divide steak mixture between warm tortillas.

name: Chicken Fajita Melts

name: Cast Iron Chicken Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless, skinless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chipotle chile powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried Mexican oregano'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'bell peppers, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, sliced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas, warmed'}
steps: Dry chicken with paper towels and pound to a uniform thickness of 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.. Combine cumin, chipotle chili powder, chili powder, smoked paprika, salt, coriander, garlic, Mexican oregano, and pepper in a bowl. Divide spice mixture in half. Sprinkle chicken with 1/2 of the spice mixture and rub on both sides of the chicken. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or up to 8 hours.. Combine bell pepper slices, onion slices, and 1 tablespoon olive oil in a bowl. Stir vegetables until coated in oil, then sprinkle reserved spice mix over the vegetables. name: Chili-Lime Shrimp Fajitas

Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat; spray with cooking spray. Add onion, green bell pepper, and serrano chile pepper; saute until tender, 10 to 12 minutes. name: Grilled Steak Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 1/4 pound)', 'name': 'flank steak'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'limes'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'green bell pepper, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'red onion, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'serving', 'name': 'olive oil cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Coat both sides of the flank steak with 1 tablespoon each salt and pepper, pressing into the steak. Place in a large freezer bag. Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Season bell pepper and red onion with salt and pepper. Place in a grill pan and set aside.. Place beans, steak, vegetables, and Mexican cheese onto the tortillas and serve.

name: Quick and Easy Baked Chicken Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken breasts, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic granules, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'dried oregano, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground cumin, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes for chili'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, cut in strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, cut into strips, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, cut into strips, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'chopped green chiles'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seasoned salt, or to taste'}
steps: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Drizzle 2 tablespoons olive oil over the bottom of a 10x14 glass dish. Add chicken strips.. steps: Flatten flank steak slightly with a meat mallet. Rub shichimi togarashi into both sides of steak, wrap the steak in plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.. Combine orange juice, soy sauce, lime juice, orange zest, and lime zest together in a resealable plastic bag. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Saute onion and red bell pepper in hot oil until soft, 5 to 10 minutes. Add sliced steak, chili powder mixture, and water to the skillet. Cook until sauce thickens and meat is glossy, 3 to 5 minutes.

Grilled Shrimp Fajitas

name: Easy Grilled Shrimp Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, sliced into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, sliced into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, sliced into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'fresh jalapeno pepper, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fajita seasoning mix, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'raw large shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'fajita-size flour tortillas'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Place bell pepper strips, onion, and jalapeno slices in a large bowl. Add 2 teaspoons of fajita seasoning and olive oil. Stir until evenly combined.. Place shrimp in a separate bowl. Add remaining 1/2 teaspoon fajita seasoning and lime juice. Gently stir until evenly combined.. Place vegetable mixture in a grill basket. Grill for 10 minutes. Stir in shrimp and grill for 5 minutes more. Remove basket from the grill.. Place tortillas on the grill and toast for 2 minutes. Divide filling between the tortillas and serve.

name: Tempeh Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'corn oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'tempeh, broken into bite-sized pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms, drained'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped green chile peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried minced onion'}
steps: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Saute tempeh with soy sauce and lime juice until tempeh browns. Stir in bell peppers, mushrooms, spinach, chile peppers, cilantro and dried onion.. Increase heat to medium-high and cook until fluids have reduced, stirring occasionally.

name: Chicken Fajita Bake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'tomato, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(1.27 ounce) packets', 'name': 'fajita seasoning'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'corn tortillas, cut in quarters'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'pinto beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}
steps: Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking pan.. Heat a skillet over medium heat. Add chicken; cook and stir until browned on all sides, about 6 minutes. Transfer chicken to a plate.. Heat oil in the hot skillet. Add tomato, bell pepper, and onion; cook and stir until softened, 5 to 7 minutes. Mix in cooked chicken, water, and fajita seasoning.. Line the bottom of the prepared pan with 5 tortillas; pour pinto beans on top. Spread 1/2 of the chicken mixture over the beans; cover with Cheddar cheese. Layer the remaining tortillas, black beans, and chicken mixture on top. Cover with aluminum foil.. Bake in the preheated oven until tortillas are lightly browned and chicken juices run clear, 25 to 30 minutes. Top with green onions and cilantro.

name: Shrimp Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'medium shrimp - peeled, deveined, and tails removed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'red bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'orange bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'red onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'fajita-size flour tortillas, warmed'}
steps: Whisk chili powder, olive oil, lime juice, and garlic salt together in a medium bowl. Add shrimp and toss to coat. Let marinate for 10 minutes.. While shrimp marinates, heat a large skillet or griddle over medium-high heat. Spray with cooking spray. Add bell peppers and onion; saute until tender, 7 to 8 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and cover with foil to keep warm.. Pour shrimp and the marinade into the same skillet. Cook shrimp until they are bright pink on the outside and the meat is opaque, about 2 minutes per side.. Serve shrimp, onion, and peppers in flour tortillas.

name: 20-Minute Shrimp Fajitas Sheet Pan Dinner
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'uncooked medium shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'yellow bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'orange bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'lime, juiced, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas, warmed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado, sliced, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Spray a rimmed baking sheet with cooking spray.. Combine shrimp, bell peppers, red onion, olive oil, chili powder, salt, black pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, cumin, and paprika in a large bowl; toss to combine. Spread mixture on the prepared pan evenly.. Cook in the preheated oven until shrimp are bright pink and firm, about 8 minutes. Turn on the oven's broiler and cook for an additional 2 minutes.. Squeeze lime juice over mixture.. Build fajitas on tortillas with avocado slices and cilantro.

name: Air Fryer Turkey Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried Mexican oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'limes, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'skinless, boneless turkey breast, cut into 1/2-inch thick slices'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'red bell pepper, sliced into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'yellow bell pepper, sliced into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'red onion, halved and sliced into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, seeded and chopped, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: Mix chili powder, cumin, paprika, oregano, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder together in a small bowl. Squeeze the juice of 1 lime over the turkey breast. Sprinkle seasoning mixture over the meat. Add 1 tablespoon oil. Toss to coat and set aside.. Place bell peppers and onion into a bowl and cover with remaining oil. Toss to coat.. Preheat an air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions.. Cook the bell peppers and onion in the preheated air fryer for 8 minutes. Shake and cook another 5 minutes. Add jalapenos. Cook for 5 minutes. Open the basket, shake, and place turkey strips in one single layer on top of the vegetables. Close the basket and cook, 7 to 8 minutes. Open, shake the basket to distribute mixture, and continue to cook until turkey strips are a bit crispy and no longer pink in the centers and peppers are tender, about 5 minutes more.. Remove the basket and place the fajitas in a bowl or on a platter. Top with cilantro and squeeze juice of remaining lime over.

name: Barbeque Pork Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless pork chops, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic pepper blend'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion slices'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'barbeque sauce'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Combine pork strips, cumin, and garlic pepper blend in a large resealable plastic bag. Shake until pork is coated.. Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add pork; cook and stir until browned, 4 to 5 minutes. Add onion, red bell pepper, and green bell pepper; cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Stir in barbeque sauce; simmer until flavors combine, about 2 minutes.. Serve pork mixture over flour tortillas.

name: Garlic Onion Chicken Fajitas with Lime
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'orange juice'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried minced onion'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried cilantro leaves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'coarsely ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Whisk orange juice, lime juice, olive oil, garlic, dried onion, oregano, cilantro, salt, and black pepper together in a bowl until marinade is smooth. Measure out 1/4 cup of the marinade and set aside. Pour remaining marinade into a resealable plastic bag, place chicken in the bag, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate chicken in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.. Remove chicken from marinade and shake off excess; discard remaining marinade.. Cook and stir chicken in a large skillet over medium-high heat until lightly browned and cooked through, 3 to 7 minutes. Transfer chicken to a plate. Cook and stir pepper and onion in the same skillet with reserved 1/4 cup of marinade until vegetables are tender and liquid is reduced, about 5 minutes. Return chicken to skillet; cook and stir until heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.. Spoon chicken mixture into tortillas.

name: Heinz® Classic Family Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onions, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'sweet peppers, sliced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground turkey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'Heinz® Chili Sauce, Chunky with Sweet Peppers'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Heinz Tomato Ketchup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded old Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded lettuce'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-fat sour cream'}
steps: Heat half the oil over medium-high heat. Add onions, peppers and half of the salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes or until tender. Reserve.. Add remaining oil to pan. Crumble in turkey, add garlic, chili powder and remaining salt and pepper. Saute until brown, about 5 minutes. Stir in half the chili sauce and all of the ketchup. Bring to a simmer.. Serve meat and vegetable mixtures with tortillas and bowls of remaining chili sauce, cheese, lettuce and sour cream to make your own fajitas.

name: Cinnamon and Lime Chicken Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'boneless, skinless chicken breast halves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'baking potatoes, peeled and cubed'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'yellow onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large clove', 'name': 'garlic, peeled and minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped jalapeno peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'corn tortillas, warmed'}
steps: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Place potatoes in a shallow baking dish. Drizzle with about 1/2 the oil, and season with salt. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in the preheated oven, until tender.. Meanwhile, season chicken with cinnamon, salt, and pepper. Arrange in a separate baking dish, and bake 30 minutes in the preheated oven, until no longer pink and juices run clear. Cool and shred.. Heat remaining oil in a skillet over medium heat, and saute onion and garlic until tender. Mix in shredded chicken, jalapeno, and lime juice. Cook until heated through.. Serve the chicken and potatoes in warmed tortillas.

name: Smoky Avocado Fajitas (Meatless)
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'liquid smoke flavoring (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(1 ounce) packages', 'name': 'fajita seasoning'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'avocados - peeled, pitted, and sliced into 1/2-inch wedges'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'bell peppers - stemmed, seeded, and sliced into 1/2-inch wedges'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'extra large', 'name': 'onion, sliced into rings and rings separated'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Whisk water, oil, liquid smoke, and fajita seasoning together in a bowl and pour into a resealable plastic bag. Add avocados, bell pepper, and onion, coat with the marinade, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator for 1 hour to overnight; turn occasionally.. Preheat oven to 225 degrees F (110 degrees C). Stack tortillas; wrap in aluminum foil. Place in oven to warm.. Preheat grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Drain marinade from vegetable mixture; transfer to a plate. Separate avocados from onions and bell peppers.. Place onions and peppers, in 1 layer, onto grill using tongs; cook until tender, 5 to 10 minutes, turning as needed. Transfer to an oven-proof pan; cover with aluminum foil. Place in the preheated oven to keep warm.. Place avocados in 1 layer onto grill; cook, turning once, until browned, about 5 minutes.. Fill tortillas with avocado and onion mixture; roll or fold tortilla around filling.

name: Easy Sheet Pan Shrimp Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'jumbo shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon-pepper seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onions, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell peppers, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'fajita seasoning'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a large sheet pan with cooking spray.. Mix shrimp and lemon-pepper seasoning together in a bowl.. Toss onions and bell pepper strips with olive oil and fajita seasoning in a large bowl until thoroughly coated. Arrange shrimp on one side of the prepared pan and vegetables on the other.. Bake in the preheated oven until shrimp are bright pink on the outside and the meat is opaque, about 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, stack tortillas on a microwave-safe plate and cover with a wet paper towel. Heat in the microwave for 45 seconds. Serve with shrimp fajitas.

name: Cyndi's Shrimp Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'large shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'zucchini, cubed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) box', 'name': 'frozen corn'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: In a medium bowl, combine the Worcestershire, lime juice, soy sauce, and chile powder. Add the shrimp and marinate 15 minutes.. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook the zucchini, onion, and corn for 10 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. Cover to keep warm and set aside.. In a separate skillet heat olive oil over medium heat. Add the shrimp and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, until the shrimp are pink. Combine the shrimp and the vegetables. Place shrimp and vegetable mixture in tortillas; sprinkle with the Monterey Jack cheese and cilantro.

name: Mango Salsa Steak Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'Old El Paso® taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 1/4 pound)', 'name': 'flank steak, trimmed of excess fat'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'Old El Paso® flour tortillas for soft tacos & fajitas'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ripe medium mangoes, seed removed, peeled and diced'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Juice of 1 medium lime'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno chile, seeded, chopped'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped red onion'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro leaves'}
steps: Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Line cookie sheet with foil.. In 10-inch skillet, heat oil over high heat. Sprinkle taco seasoning mix over flank steak, pressing to coat. Brown steak in oil on both sides. Place steak on cookie sheet. Roast until meat thermometer inserted in center of steak reads 135 degrees F. Remove from oven, and let rest 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, in large bowl, mix salsa ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.. Cut steak into thin slices. Place 2 or 3 slices steak on each tortilla. Top with salsa. Roll up tortillas.

name: Air-Fried Shrimp Fajitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'large shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red bell pepper, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'green bell pepper, cut into thin strips'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'family-style fajita seasoning (such as Savory Spice Shop®), or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'flour tortillas, warmed'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 3 minutes.. Combine shrimp, onion, and bell peppers in a bowl and lightly coat with oil spray. Sprinkle fajita seasoning over the shrimp mixture; mix to combine. Transfer into the air fryer basket.. Air fry for 8 minutes. Squeeze lime juice over the shrimp mixture. Serve immediately with warm tortillas.
